THE ANC in KZN has promised to take serious action against a councillor and other officials.They were bust for earning money as ghost employees of Harry Gwala Municipality in Ixopo.On Thursday, Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma municipal councillor, Nomalungelo Magoso, was found guilty and sentenced to five years or a R50 000 fine by the Durban Specialised Commercial Crimes Court. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Before being appointed as councillor after the local government elections, she was working in water and sanitation at the district municipality. Last year, it was found she was being paid two salaries as a district municipal employee while earning a salary as a councillor.Municipal spokesman Ndabezitha Tenza said they are happy the councillor has been punished. He said the four officials who allegedly paid the ghost employees were suspended.ANC provincial interim committee spokesman Super Zuma said the party was disappointed to find its councillor involved in the taking of taxpayers’ money. “We have instructed officials to deal with those involved through internal disciplinary processes.” Municipal manager Nkosiyezwe Vezi said Magoso was found guilty on Thursday. “Although she paid the fine, it’s not over yet because we must still take disciplinary action against her,” said Vezi.